question_text: Explain the concept of redundancy in robotic manipulators. Discuss the advantages and challenges associated with redundant robots.
option_1: Redundancy allows robots to perform multiple tasks simultaneously; challenges include increased computational complexity.
option_2: Redundancy improves precision in trajectory tracking; challenges include limited workspace.
option_3: Redundancy increases payload capacity; challenges include decreased flexibility.
option_4: Redundancy provides fault tolerance; challenges include reduced operational speed.

option_1: A point in the robot's workspace where the end-effector cannot reach.
option_2: A configuration where the Jacobian matrix becomes non-invertible.
option_3: The maximum payload capacity of a robotic arm.
